init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The Russians were busy taking up all of Europe, and the Chinese had already colonized Africa.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Hadronium was a block of solid fuel that could be used as a power source for anything from cars to spaceships.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: When America exited isolation, Canada convinced them that they had done a better job of protecting Alaska than the Americans.
